[2026-04-14T11:09:22.398Z] [INFO]             "text": "Here is the comparison summary:\n\n---\n\n## Workflow Files\n\n**JS template** (`js-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template`):\n- `release.yml` (single workflow, not split by language)\n- `links.yml`\n\n**Rust template** (`rust-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template`):\n- `release.yml`\n\n**Current project** (`/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1776164796151/.github/workflows/`):\n- `js.yml`\n- `rust.yml`\n\n---\n\n## Key Differences: Release/Publish Steps\n\n### 1. `check-changesets` step is missing in `js.yml`\nThe JS template's `release` job uses a dedicated script step:\n```yaml\n- name: Check for changesets\n  id: check_changesets\n  run: node scripts/check-changesets.mjs\n```\nThe current `js.yml` inlines this as a bash `find` command instead. The template also has a `merge-changesets.mjs` step that runs when `changeset_count > 1` — this step is **absent in `js.yml`**.\n\n### 2. Node.js version: `20.x` (template) vs `22.x` (js.yml)\nTemplate uses Node 20, current project uses Node 22 everywhere.\n\n### 3. Concurrency behavior on `main`\nTemplate uses `cancel-in-progress: ${{ github.ref == 'refs/heads/main' }}` (cancels on main, queues on PRs). Current `js.yml` uses `cancel-in-progress: true` unconditionally — meaning concurrent pushes to main can cancel an in-progress release.\n\n### 4. Missing fast checks in `js.yml`\nTemplate has extra jobs absent from `js.yml`:\n- `test-compilation` (syntax-checks `.mjs` files)\n- `check-file-line-limits` (enforces 1500-line limit)\n- `version-check` (blocks manual version bumps in PRs)\n- `validate-docs`\n- `simulate-fresh-merge.sh` steps before lint/test\n\n### 5. `test` job matrix\nTemplate: 3 OS x 3 runtimes (node/bun/deno = 9 jobs). Current `js.yml`: only `ubuntu-latest` with node only.\n\n### 6. `test` job dependencies\nTemplate `test` also depends on `test-compilation` and `check-file-line-limits` before running. `js.yml` only depends on `detect-changes` and `changeset-check`.\n\n---\n\n## Scripts: setup-npm, publish-to-npm, detect-code-changes\n\nAll three exist in **both** the JS template and the current project:\n\n| Script | JS Template | Current Project |\n|---|---|---|\n| `setup-npm.mjs` | yes | yes (`/tmp/.../scripts/setup-npm.mjs`) |\n| `publish-to-npm.mjs` | yes | yes |\n| `detect-code-changes.mjs` | yes | yes |\n| `check-changesets.mjs` | yes | **missing** from current project |\n| `merge-changesets.mjs` | yes | **missing** from current project |\n| `simulate-fresh-merge.sh` | yes | **missing** |\n| `check-file-line-limits.sh` | yes | **missing** |\n| `check-mjs-syntax.sh` | yes | **missing** |\n| `check-version.mjs` | yes | **missing** |\n| `validate-changeset.mjs` | yes | yes |\n\n---\n\n## Actionable Differences to Address\n\n1. **Add `check-changesets.mjs` and `merge-changesets.mjs`** to `scripts/` — the inline bash in `js.yml` is less robust and lacks multi-changeset merging.\n2. **Fix concurrency** on `main` — change `cancel-in-progress: true` to `cancel-in-progress: ${{ github.ref == 'refs/heads/main' }}` to avoid cancelling live releases.\n3. **Add `version-check` job** to `js.yml` to block manual version edits in PRs.\n4. **Add fast-check jobs** (`test-compilation`, `check-file-line-limits`) and the `simulate-fresh-merge.sh` step before lint/test.\n5. **Expand test matrix** if multi-runtime/OS coverage is desired."
