[2026-04-14T11:10:15.592Z] [INFO]         "text": "Now I have a thorough understanding of all the issues. Let me summarize and start implementing.\n\n## Root Cause Analysis Summary\n\nI identified **3 root cause failures** in the CI/CD:\n\n### 1. `setup-npm.mjs` — All npm upgrade fallbacks fail (CRITICAL)\nNode.js 22.22.2 on GitHub Actions ships with a broken npm 10.9.7 missing the `promise-retry` module. The script has 3 fallbacks (npm install -g, npx, corepack) but all fail. The script doesn't exit with error — it continues, leaving npm at 10.9.7 which doesn't support OIDC trusted publishing. The template doesn't have this fix either — it uses `npm install -g npm@latest` with no fallbacks.\n\n### 2. `publish-to-npm.mjs` — npm publish gets 404 from registry\n`npm publish --provenance --access public` returns `404 Not Found - PUT` from npmjs.org. Since npm is still at 10.9.7 (no OIDC support), the publish fails. The error handler for 404 (first-time publish) doesn't trigger because `command-stream`'s `$` throws before the catch can analyze the error message properly.\n\n### 3. `cancel-in-progress: true` on main — Can cancel active releases\nWhen a version bump commit is pushed to main during release, it triggers a new workflow run that cancels the current one.\n\nLet me implement the fixes."
[2026-04-14T11:10:15.592Z] [INFO]       }
