[2026-04-14T11:12:06.674Z] [INFO]         "text": "Now let me also check the detect-changes issue more carefully. The log showed it detected the push as a \"Merge commit\" and compared `HEAD^2^` to `HEAD^2`, finding only `.gitkeep` changed. That's actually correct behavior — it only detected the last commit's changes. But the issue is that the **release job still ran** even though detect-changes said `any-js-code-changed=false`. Let me check why.\n\nLooking at the workflow: the release job depends on `lint` and `test`, NOT on `detect-changes`. And `lint` runs when `any-js-code-changed == 'true'` OR on push events (line 108: `github.event_name == 'push'`). So on push to main, lint and test always run, and therefore release always runs too.\n\nThe release job has its own changeset check (line 224: `find .changeset -name \"*.md\" ! -name \"README.md\"`). If there's a changeset file present, it proceeds with versioning and publishing. The issue is that the merge commit that triggered this was the merge of PR #54 which included a changeset file. So the release correctly tried to version and publish — the problem is purely with npm being broken.\n\nLet me commit these fixes and then create the case study."
[2026-04-14T11:12:06.674Z] [INFO]       }
