[2026-04-14T11:12:18.172Z] [INFO]           "command": "git add .github/workflows/js.yml scripts/setup-npm.mjs scripts/publish-to-npm.mjs && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nFix JS CI/CD: npm upgrade fallbacks, publish error detection, and concurrency\n\nRoot causes from CI runs 24391258731 and 24394459276:\n1. setup-npm.mjs: All npm upgrade fallbacks fail on GitHub Actions with\n   Node.js 22.22.2 (broken npm 10.9.7 missing promise-retry module).\n   Added Strategy 2: direct tarball download via curl that bypasses npm entirely.\n   Now exits with error instead of silently continuing with broken npm.\n2. publish-to-npm.mjs: 404 error from npm publish was not caught because\n   command-stream's $ throws before the catch block can analyze the error.\n   Switched to .run({ capture: true }) for reliable output-based error detection.\n3. js.yml: cancel-in-progress:true on main could cancel active releases\n   when version bump commits trigger new workflow runs.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\"",
