[2026-04-14T11:14:55.138Z] [INFO]           "command": "gh pr edit 55 --repo link-assistant/web-capture --title \"Fix JS CI/CD: npm upgrade, publish error detection, and concurrency\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\nFixes #52\n\n- **`setup-npm.mjs`**: Added direct tarball download via `curl` as fallback strategy for upgrading npm when the bundled npm 10.9.7 is broken (missing `promise-retry` module on Node.js 22.22.2 GitHub Actions runners). Also changed to exit with error instead of silently continuing with broken npm.\n- **`publish-to-npm.mjs`**: Switched `npm publish` invocation from `await $\\`...\\`` (throws before error analysis) to `.run({ capture: true })` for reliable 404 error detection and actionable first-time publish guidance.\n- **`js.yml`**: Changed `cancel-in-progress: true` to `cancel-in-progress: ${{ github.ref != 'refs/heads/main' }}` to prevent cancellation of active release workflows when version bump commits trigger new runs.\n\n## Root Causes\n\n1. **`setup-npm.mjs`** — All 3 npm upgrade strategies (npm install -g, npx, corepack) fail on GitHub Actions with Node.js 22.22.2 due to [actions/runner-images#13883](https://github.com/actions/runner-images/issues/13883). Script continued silently with broken npm.\n2. **`publish-to-npm.mjs`** — `command-stream`'s `$` template tag throws on non-zero exit before the catch block can analyze the error message for 404 patterns.\n3. **`js.yml`** — `cancel-in-progress: true` on main could cancel active releases when version bump commits trigger new workflow runs.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] CI passes on this PR (lint, test jobs)\n- [ ] Verify `setup-npm.mjs` curl fallback works by checking npm version in release job logs\n- [ ] Verify `publish-to-npm.mjs` provides clear 404 error message instead of retrying\n- [ ] Verify release workflow on main is not cancelled by version bump commits\n\nSee [docs/case-studies/issue-52/README.md](docs/case-studies/issue-52/README.md) for full analysis with timeline, template comparison, and CI logs.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1",
