[2026-04-14T11:15:31.187Z] [INFO]           "command": "gh issue create --repo link-foundation/js-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template \\\n  --title \"setup-npm.mjs: npm upgrade fails on GitHub Actions with Node.js 22.22.2 (broken npm 10.9.7)\" \\\n  --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Problem\n\n`setup-npm.mjs` fails to upgrade npm on GitHub Actions runners with Node.js 22.22.2. The bundled npm 10.9.7 is missing the `promise-retry` module, causing `npm install -g npm@latest` to fail with `MODULE_NOT_FOUND`.\n\nThis means `npm publish --provenance` (OIDC trusted publishing) fails because it requires npm >= 11.5.1.\n\n## Reproduction\n\nRun a GitHub Actions workflow on `ubuntu-latest` with `node-version: '22.x'` that calls `node scripts/setup-npm.mjs`:\n\n```\nnpm error code MODULE_NOT_FOUND\nnpm error Cannot find module 'promise-retry'\nnpm error Require stack:\nnpm error - /opt/hostedtoolcache/node/22.22.2/x64/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/@npmcli/arborist/lib/arborist/rebuild.js\n```\n\n## Upstream Issues\n\n- [actions/runner-images#13883](https://github.com/actions/runner-images/issues/13883)\n- [nodejs/node#62430](https://github.com/nodejs/node/issues/62430)\n- [npm/cli#9151](https://github.com/npm/cli/issues/9151)\n\n## Workaround\n\nDownload npm tarball directly via `curl`, bypassing the broken npm entirely:\n\n```javascript\nconst nodeDir = run(\"dirname $(dirname $(which node))\");\nconst globalNpmDir = `${nodeDir}/lib/node_modules/npm`;\nrun(\n  `curl -sL https://registry.npmjs.org/npm/-/npm-11.4.2.tgz | ` +\n  `tar xz -C /tmp && ` +\n  `rm -rf \"${globalNpmDir}\" && ` +\n  `mv /tmp/package \"${globalNpmDir}\"`\n);\n```\n\n## Suggested Fix\n\nAdd the curl-based tarball download as a fallback strategy in `setup-npm.mjs` (between the standard `npm install -g` and the npx/corepack fallbacks). Also exit with error code 1 when all strategies fail instead of silently continuing with broken npm.\n\nSee [link-assistant/web-capture#55](https://github.com/link-assistant/web-capture/pull/55) for a reference implementation.\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1",
