[2026-04-14T11:15:44.463Z] [INFO]           "command": "gh issue create --repo link-foundation/js-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template \\\n  --title \"Workflow concurrency: cancel-in-progress on main can cancel active releases\" \\\n  --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Problem\n\nThe `release.yml` workflow uses:\n\n```yaml\nconcurrency:\n  group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}\n  cancel-in-progress: ${{ github.ref == 'refs/heads/main' }}\n```\n\nThis cancels in-progress runs **on main** — which is exactly where releases happen. When the version-and-commit step pushes a new commit to main, it triggers a new workflow run that may cancel the currently running release before publish completes.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\n- **Main branch:** Never cancel active runs (releases should complete)\n- **PR branches:** Cancel stale runs when new commits are pushed\n\n## Suggested Fix\n\nInvert the condition:\n\n```yaml\nconcurrency:\n  group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}\n  cancel-in-progress: ${{ github.ref != 'refs/heads/main' }}\n```\n\n## Reference\n\nSee [link-assistant/web-capture#55](https://github.com/link-assistant/web-capture/pull/55) for the same fix applied in a downstream project.\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1",
[2026-04-14T11:15:44.463Z] [INFO]           "description": "Create issue on JS template about concurrency bug"
